defaultRMT believe t
defaulthat a single death is a death too many and the level of fatalities associated with level crossings must be reduced
default by the rail industry.
default1.4
default 
defaultAfter fatalities associated with suicide and trespass on the railway, level crossings represent the highest risk on
default the GB rail network.
default1.5
default 
defaultSince 2004 RMT have 
defaultadopted
default a policy that calls on the rail industry to develop a programme to eliminate level crossings from high-speed railway lines, replacing them with underpasses or bridges, and for a feasibility study on the
default rest of the network with the ultimate aim of removing all level crossings from Britain’s rail network.
