default2.1 
defaultUltimately the most cost effective solution is permanent closure of all level crossings.
default3.1 
defaultRMT believes that all level crossings
default should be closed and that Network Rail should
default be
default required to deliver a plan to maximise the reduction in level crossings, and consequently accidents, by ring-fencing a substantial portion of its expenditure for that specific purpose. RMT believes that the
default £67m ring-fenced fund suggested in ORR’s draft determination is inadequate.
default 
default3.2
default 
defaultOf course the issue of prioritising expenditure on improving level crossing safety cannot be separated from the wider public debate about the structure of the industry. Indep
defaultendent reports state that costs of the privatised and fragmented rail system amount to £1.2bn a year compared 
defaultto 
defaultif the industry was in public 
defaultownership.
default 
default Even by making some 
defaultinternal structural reforms Network Rail could save considerable amounts
default. Bringi
defaultng rail maintenance in
default 
defaulthouse for example saved £400m
default a year and it is estimated that taking similar steps in respect of rail renewals could save £200m.
default3.3 
defaultCurrently ORR and Network Rail have provisions to open new level crossings and allow land developm
defaultent in the vicinity of level crossings. 
defaultRMT believe that there should be no new level crossings brought into use on the railway network and further believe any development in the geographical vicinity of existing level crossings should be resisted if it ca
defaultn be shown that such development 
defaultwould result in an increase in
default road
default traffic over the level crossing.
default 
default3.4 For example in a case where an industrial estate has its access over a level crossing and the owners wish to expand the estate then they should be prevented from expansion unless another form of access can be provided which results in the level crossin
defaultg closure. 
default3.4 
defaultORR policy is that new level crossings can be allowed in certain circumstances such as if a crossing becomes unsafe or a previously closed crossing is brought back into service. RMT believe this policy is wrong.
